cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

This paper is primarily focused on natural language processing (NLP) and specifically on neural machine translation (NMT) systems. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) to augment the NMT model, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of the relationship between the gains obtained and properties of the target language, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
